# If you are unfamiliar with words or idioms, you guess at their meaning, using clues presented in the context.
On the assumption that they will become relevant later, you make a mental note of discourse entities as well as possible links between them.

# You make further inferences, for instance, about how the text may be significant to you, or about its validity-inferences that form the basis of a personal response 
for which the author will inevitably be far less responsible.

# Rather, we ascribe meanings to texts on the basis of interaction between what we might call textual and contextual material: between what 
